text: Predicted movie plot: the film begins with a hilarious comparison of the human genes being created from it's cellular stages but one small yellow blob escapes and evolves on it's own this creating the minions. They rise from the sea and search for a villain to serve through a long montage but everyone fails. They then come to the North Pole and go on one last resort to find a master for the rest of the minions. The three arrive in America where they come across a few funny shinagins and then they see a poster revealing scarlet overkill at a villain exhibition. We get a sneak peek at gru trying to look appealing but is overlooked by the minions because they favour overkill. She recruits them because to her they look manipulative. She tests out their skills and despite the clumsiness they got the task done. She then prepares to steal the crown....the minions go, retrieve it give it to her, she wants to destroy the world with it because that's how it works. The minions roll around in success, they lose their sense of purpose and then in a long gibberish speech they realise they need to save their kind so they head to Scarlett where they discover her evil plans and therefore try to defeat her. They look like they will lose but through a funny 'ex machina' they defeat her and the world is saved because a villain cannot exist if there is no world. They leave in their victory yet disappointed that they lost another boss. So they head back to the exhibition and gru to the small audience reveals his plan for talking the moon, the crowd laughs but one of the three minions is in love with the moon so he joins and soon they all join. ...will this happen?...

text: 1:30 "Hello, Papagayna. Tu les bella comme la papaya." Sounds like "Hello, Papagayna. You are beautiful as the papaya."  Tu - familiar form of "you" in many european languages Les - plural article in french, but sounds kind of like "es" or "is" in french Bella - "beauty" in italian Comme - "like" in french La - feminine article in many european languages Papaya - the fruit
